text:
OpenSSL 1.1.1c now introduces Brexit_EU_DBRG, a pseudo-random number generator based on the analysis of the state of Brexit at any given time.

The internal entropy state can be obtained by checking the value of the global variable "meaningful_vote" which increments with entropy.
retweet_text:
OpenSSL 1.1.1c now introduces Brexit_EU_DBRG, a pseudo-random number generator based on the analysis of the state of Brexit at any given time.

The internal entropy state can be obtained by checking the value of the global variable "meaningful_vote" which increments with entropy.

text:
Fellow neat-freaks!

Add this to your .bash_profile and thank me later.

alias gcmb="git branch --merged | grep -Ev '(^\*|master)' | xargs git branch -d"

It cleans all branches you’ve got locally that have already been merged.

#rstats shiny tip of the day:

You should not have a render*() function inside a reactive() or an observe(). If you find yourself nesting output render functions inside reactive/observe:

STOP.

It's almost always an incorrect approach to reactivity.
